Tomb Toad packs plenty of challenge. Recent updates have gone a long way to smoothing out the difficulty. Hidden levels and a map editor offer long term replay value.

absolutely amazing. one of the best games I've played my phone phone if not THE best. the levels are hard but not impossible, they will definitely keep you busy! one gripe that I do have (it's not really a gripe, it's just me being a bit OCD) is that it would be great for it to be optimised for larger screens that have those annoying notches. because at the moment there's a gap where the game and the notch is. other than that I'm extremely looking forward to further updates and content!
I don't normally review games, but this game is awesome. - It's unique - challenging - creative Like an 8 Bit Dark Souls Puzzler for kids
Really fun, I've enjoyed playing it. Nice, simple, but challenging levels. Very clean and attractive art-style
Like the concept. Love the graphics and music. Not a fan of the difficulty spike
Great game that mixes light dungeon crawling and puzzling using beautiful minimal graphics.

Exceptional game! You should contact Snoman Gaming on YouTube and ask whether he can feature your game ;). My only gripes in this toadally awesome game are the lack of controller support and the missing feature to save the game's files on the phone's external storage. I'm also not sure whether the game supports cloud saving. I would really appreciate if you could add these features in the future :). P.s: there is a bug in 14-5 (the center square gets stuck at the wall and can't flip the switch).
Looks simple, but far from that! Clever level design, challenging puzzles, and really liking the gameboy graphic design! Spike in level design! Level 2.4 is way too difficult.
Amazing feel and unique gameplay, love it!
The map maker is great! Very easy to build your own levels. Cool retromodern puzzle game.

Simple, single touch, intuitive gameplay that never loses its intrigue thanks to ever evolving hazards and level layouts. A catchy soundtrack, stylish graphics, and the creative uses of the core mechanic make for an extremely satisfying experience. This is what mobile games are supposed to be.

Seems really simple at first, but becomes very challenging quickly and keeps me glued to the screen trying to overcome each level! Awesome, original gameplay mechanics and includes the ability to create your own levels and share with others! Highly recommend this game!
This game hard as hell I love it

There's a fascination with going back to an art presentation of the 1bit era, but using the power of modern computing to add a new dimension... Tomb Toad has a familiarity, but smashing in a seamless isometric 3D effect. The results are anomalous... Downwell, Minit, they've all brought 1bit back, but Tomb Toad leads the way with its unique presentation. Add to this, solid "ond more go" gameplay and even your own level editor... NOT TO BE MISSED!
